description:
Ensure reading ticks with Manual=true works correctly with new awaiting system

When loading a tick:
- If Manual=true AND Awaiting is null, treat as Awaiting="work"
- This is handled by IsAwaitingHuman() and GetAwaitingType() helpers
- No data migration needed for reads

Implementation:
The helper methods in tick.go handle this:

func (t *Tick) IsAwaitingHuman() bool {
    if t.Awaiting != nil && *t.Awaiting != "" {
        return true
    }
    return t.Manual  // Backwards compat
}

func (t *Tick) GetAwaitingType() string {
    if t.Awaiting != nil && *t.Awaiting != "" {
        return *t.Awaiting
    }
    if t.Manual {
        return AwaitingWork  // Backwards compat
    }
    return ""
}

All code should use these helpers rather than accessing fields directly.
